Notebook[{
Cell["The Stabilizer Formalism, by Computation", "Title",ExpressionUUID->"cdc7198b-2e05-43c4-9eab-9d412fc45e21"],

Cell["\<\
This document teaches the stabilizer formalism the way one would teach it at \
a chalkboard with a kernel open: every claim is immediately computed. We \
start from the observation that a single qubit can be specified not by its \
two amplitudes but by the one operator that fixes it, build that idea into \
the Aaronson-Gottesman tableau, and ride it all the way to thousand-qubit \
Clifford circuits, error-correcting codes, graph states, magic states, and \
Clifford channels. We close with a measured, honest comparison against the \
specialized C++ and Julia stabilizer simulators.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"83c6e9e0-beae-4e81-9703-be77bc398473"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The arc is: a state is what stabilizes it (single qubit), ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["n", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "71318c12-a1f6-46d6-8e90-ead716080189"],
 " generators replace ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SuperscriptBox["2", 
   StyleBox["n", "TI"]]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "d9396d5f-f732-4e54-943b-902578ddb982"],
 " amplitudes (the tableau), entanglement and measurement become linear \
algebra over ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SubscriptBox["\|01d53d", "2"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "a72a7a2d-0770-49f6-af61-72a993b6d603"],
 " (the field of two elements ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"{", "0"}], ",", 
   RowBox[{"1", "}"}]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "25c1869c-3715-4ddd-b97e-838a967f6816"],
 " with all arithmetic done mod 2, so that ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"1", "+", "1", "=", "0"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "6ba6c6be-42c2-4114-a63f-dae216dbcf24"],
 " and vector addition is the bitwise XOR), and then scale, codes, and the \
frontier. The audience is graduate students who know quantum mechanics and \
the Pauli group but have not yet seen why a stabilizer state of a thousand \
qubits is something you can hold in your hand. Every construction in this \
document is built explicitly so you can change it, break it, and extend it. \
The ",
 ButtonBox["Wolfram QuantumFramework",
  BaseStyle->"Hyperlink",
  ButtonData->{
    URL["https://resources.wolframcloud.com/PacletRepository/resources/\
Wolfram/QuantumFramework/"], None}],
 " symbols we exercise live in the ",
 ButtonBox["Wolfram QuantumFramework",
  BaseStyle->"Hyperlink",
  ButtonData->{
    URL["https://resources.wolframcloud.com/PacletRepository/resources/\
Wolfram/QuantumFramework/"], None}],
 " paclet; the central one is PauliStabilizer."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"aa3e99b6-1659-4a17-b9b1-91c1584fc6d2"],

Cell["Setup", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"10b91dc7-b313-4f8a-ab66-ca59b69f82f4"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "We load the framework from the working tree so the fast paths and recent \
fixes are present. On a current release, the plain ",
 Cell[BoxData["Needs"], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "00ca6bdd-6357-4630-afa0-1a85fc4d59c8"],
 " line alone suffices."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"483b46d8-5b00-4f1c-b48f-f0f4c14176ca"],

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
  "PacletDirectoryLoad", 
   "[", "\"\</Users/mohammadb/Documents/GitHub/QuantumFramework/\
QuantumFramework\>\"", "]"}], ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{"Needs", "[", "\"\<Wolfram`QuantumFramework`\>\"", "]"}]}], "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[1]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"1ec72e58-1020-46a0-a3d3-6ec433634698"],

Cell["The core functions at a glance", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"0c8e95c4-2407-403a-ad2e-7e01bdac761e"],

Cell["\<\
Before the narrative, the whole working surface, grouped by task. Every call \
is exercised in context where it is introduced; this is the map.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"4dea813e-9445-418b-a2de-f42fe8a7d588"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Construct", "TI"],
 " a register, from signed Pauli strings, a named code, or a random Clifford: \
",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"PauliStabilizer", "[", "n", "]"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "c73826be-0f1f-4136-93c2-55f511523581"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"PauliStabilizer", "[", 
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{"\"\<XX\>\"", ",", " ", "\"\<ZZ\>\""}], "}"}], "]"}]], 
  "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "a84fc758-44e1-49fb-bcda-82d9346637a8"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"PauliStabilizer", "[", "\"\<SteaneCode\>\"", "]"}]], 
  "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "49ff2733-0e18-4145-afc9-e89b1e4004d8"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"PauliStabilizer", "[", 
   RowBox[{"\"\<Random\>\"", "[", "n", "]"}], "]"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "0f84818d-a217-4fce-acba-1effedbf3315"],
 "."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"0208e5d2-b2b2-4b8e-8713-7eac1d59ebf5"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Apply a Clifford gate", "TI"],
 " one at a time: ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"ps", "[", 
   RowBox[{"\"\<H\>\"", ",", " ", "j"}], "]"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "6b73443c-1c78-45e6-96f1-031f0cc96fbb"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"ps", "[", 
   RowBox[{"\"\<S\>\"", ",", " ", "j"}], "]"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "de044184-6fcc-42d5-aa94-bf64eea4fb36"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"ps", "[", 
   RowBox[{"\"\<CNOT\>\"", ",", " ", "j", ",", " ", "k"}], "]"}]], 
  "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "92a9e2c1-cb7f-4451-8017-8802503747df"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"ps", "[", 
   RowBox[{"\"\<CZ\>\"", ",", " ", "j", ",", " ", "k"}], "]"}]], 
  "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "9871a118-a710-41ac-b4a2-3258dd24a7cc"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"ps", "[", 
   RowBox[{"\"\<SWAP\>\"", ",", " ", "j", ",", " ", "k"}], "]"}]], 
  "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "495369c2-e56a-4b17-b3d6-f72a76c08fdc"],
 "."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"aecea652-3e53-46fe-8fb0-38d0cecb674c"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Apply a whole circuit", "TI"],
 " as a gate list, routed through the compiled engine (bare names take \
default targets, ",
 Cell[BoxData["->"], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "e546ab96-a926-4f94-8d42-037d15f19f54"],
 " sets explicit ones): ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"ps", "[", 
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{"\"\<H\>\"", ",", " ", "\"\<CNOT\>\"", ",", " ", 
     RowBox[{"\"\<CNOT\>\"", " ", "->", " ", 
      RowBox[{"{", 
       RowBox[{"2", ",", " ", "3"}], "}"}]}]}], "}"}], "]"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "fc96842d-b375-48d4-ae10-013d406824d7"],
 "."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"2c5d569b-c04e-46a7-9820-0b06cae37aff"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Inspect", "TI"],
 ": ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"ps", "[", "\"\<Stabilizers\>\"", "]"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "b0c07c22-63d0-4e75-95bd-104e0294c38d"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"ps", "[", "\"\<Tableau\>\"", "]"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "bce00256-1002-43d6-ba11-f680c9d02930"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"ps", "[", "\"\<Matrix\>\"", "]"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "63164354-f152-4b73-96b7-d608a2dc5d27"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"ps", "[", "\"\<State\>\"", "]"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "9813cbbb-d56f-49de-b5a0-fa6e02551c54"],
 "."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"75bd44b9-e235-4112-b314-c846752a3982"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Measure", "TI"],
 ": ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"ps", "[", 
   RowBox[{"\"\<M\>\"", ",", " ", "q"}], "]"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "2bde95c4-afeb-4582-9961-25e7301d8ad7"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"ps", "[", 
   RowBox[{"\"\<M\>\"", ",", " ", "\"\<ZZ\>\""}], "]"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "94dbbfdc-1c0c-4530-8bdf-78aee48977a3"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"ps", "[", 
   RowBox[{"\"\<Expectation\>\"", ",", " ", "\"\<ZZ\>\""}], "]"}]], 
  "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "a01f6b85-52dd-4229-97ac-9dc8c2d01d93"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"ps", "[", 
   RowBox[{"\"\<SymbolicMeasure\>\"", ",", " ", "q"}], "]"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "82afedda-aec3-48fa-9c95-14dfc00451ab"],
 "."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"a2b577e1-2985-4010-b4bb-a8d121f31142"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Entanglement entropy", "TI"],
 " across a cut: ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"ps", "[", 
   RowBox[{"\"\<Entropy\>\"", ",", " ", 
    RowBox[{"{", 
     RowBox[{"1", ",", " ", "2"}], "}"}]}], "]"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "35af59f5-eb9f-4c32-a993-ec14c6660f8b"],
 "."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"36ef0e4b-ef72-4bf8-ab7c-bb33c6981bce"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Sibling heads", "TI"],
 ": ",
 Cell[BoxData["StabilizerFrame"], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "f5e39b79-36f5-4b20-9392-86bc1ac4e019"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData["CliffordChannel"], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "708da0bd-3f68-44fa-b387-00f096f0033a"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData["GraphState"], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "7561e5e6-da46-4317-9350-e81c0a383d17"],
 " with ",
 Cell[BoxData["LocalComplement"], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "b867a7be-6dbc-4029-a382-3ed704c07916"],
 ", and the predicate ",
 Cell[BoxData["StabilizerStateQ"], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "6af5ae3d-136d-4b5b-87c4-e3065937c9da"],
 "."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"4ff59249-4bfe-4af6-8f8f-87b040840b6e"],

Cell["Why stabilizers: the exponential wall", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"3100fe97-4e78-404c-b592-bbc380415ab8"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "A pure state of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["n", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "8f6ca198-71ce-4e6e-8154-7530cd39294f"],
 " qubits is a unit vector in ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SuperscriptBox["\:2102", 
   SuperscriptBox["2", 
    StyleBox["n", "TI"]]]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "e02e75b6-c2ea-4db5-baaf-f7810f7c364e"],
 ", so writing it down means storing ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SuperscriptBox["2", 
   StyleBox["n", "TI"]]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "bda3d950-882b-405c-8d76-69245da380d2"],
 " complex amplitudes. At ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["n", "TI"], "=", "20"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "52f5137e-1fc5-42e5-b9b8-0adbfeb53f86"],
 " that is already a million numbers; at ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["n", "TI"], "=", "50"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "fdbc1bec-ea5b-4ea5-aebf-5b96b3efdce6"],
 " it is about ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SuperscriptBox["10", "15"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "c518a861-9524-4687-81a5-f1d427fce5fc"],
 ", a petabyte of amplitudes even at one byte each; by ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["n", "TI"], "=", "100"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "41a42044-56e0-49b4-831f-1b76049aa235"],
 " it passes the number of atoms in a building (",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"\[Tilde]", 
   SuperscriptBox["10", "30"]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "0e6a7b68-5bda-4859-a4e4-815bc7ab12ca"],
 "). Yet many of the states we care most about, including every state any \
error-correcting code protects, are not generic: they sit at the fixed points \
of a large group of Pauli operators, and that structure can be stored in ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["O", "TI"], 
   StyleBox["(",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   SuperscriptBox[
    StyleBox["n", "TI"], "2"], 
   StyleBox[")",
    SpanMaxSize->1]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "47c6b405-a13f-4bed-8eb7-8615320f684c"],
 " bits."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"6e6885ef-1482-4e12-9f69-aa30881c1d67"],

Cell["\<\
To feel the wall, ask for the dense state vector of a 20-qubit GHZ state and \
look only at its length:\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"6adaa14b-58f4-4105-96fd-088987975461"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"Length", " ", "@", " ", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"QuantumState", "[", 
    RowBox[{"\"\<GHZ\>\"", "[", "20", "]"}], "]"}], "[", "\"\<StateVector\>\"",
    "]"}]}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[2]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"8c126abf-268b-4ec7-b5eb-8722f773883c"],

Cell[BoxData["1048576"], "Output",
 CellLabel->"Out[2]= ",ExpressionUUID->"1693b531-90da-44dc-8677-0e21fc890f23"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
 "That is ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SuperscriptBox["2", "20"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "b15375b6-7003-430d-a260-3714c20309d5"],
 " amplitudes for a state that is pinned down completely by 20 short Pauli \
strings. The stabilizer formalism is the bookkeeping that exploits exactly \
this gap."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"31c0f2e4-247b-49a1-888e-142ea492eab1"],

Cell["A state is what fixes it: the single qubit", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"5eb5ec06-8ad7-4845-9364-bd841a2cd34b"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The central move is to stop describing a state by its amplitudes and start \
describing it by the operators that leave it invariant. The state ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{"0"},
   "Ket"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "e8c3e0a9-d970-426b-9009-82b9ffa9240a"],
 " is the unique ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"+", "1"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "c80afade-03df-41f2-b536-b30c78e340dd"],
 " eigenvector of the Pauli operator ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["Z", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "d5a6cf2e-3744-46f2-b700-60134cb1e7fe"],
 ". We say ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["Z", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "9527bf3f-b0a7-47da-a262-39813fe2a2ec"],
 " ",
 StyleBox["stabilizes", "TI"],
 " ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{"0"},
   "Ket"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "7ded462e-a30f-45c5-914d-541bf3ac2e2e"],
 ", and since one operator already determines a one-qubit state up to \
normalization, that single fact ",
 StyleBox["is", "TI"],
 " the state."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"4ac42cce-3a18-4925-90a2-541ce9aca465"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "A caution that defines the whole subject: this works only for special \
states. Of all one-qubit pure states, exactly six are ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"+", "1"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "0eac2dc3-cb67-43ff-acaf-ca1cf081a700"],
 " eigenstates of a Pauli: ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{"0"},
   "Ket"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "74267e77-e5de-4abd-924e-017cfaed5883"],
 " and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{"1"},
   "Ket"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "fb118863-e8c8-4558-93a7-7b1d4c791cb6"],
 " for ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"\[PlusMinus]", 
   StyleBox["Z", "TI"]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "542a9da0-69e1-4153-9cfc-cb5cac715792"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{"\[PlusMinus]"},
   "Ket"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "901c4970-228d-4b72-994e-8d6fbc85dbce"],
 " for ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"\[PlusMinus]", 
   StyleBox["X", "TI"]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "f74335d1-3062-46c2-8205-998885e4fd1f"],
 ", and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{
    StyleBox["i", "TI"]},
   "Ket"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "17acdb2d-388d-453b-b0b3-993524174005"],
 " for ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"\[PlusMinus]", 
   StyleBox["Y", "TI"]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "d2308f74-0104-456e-a323-3da41ec1349f"],
 ". These six are the ",
 StyleBox["stabilizer states", "TI"],
 ", and the formalism is exactly their theory and its multi-qubit \
generalization; a generic ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{
    StyleBox["cos",
     FontSlant->"Plain"], 
    StyleBox["\[Theta]", "TI"], 
    TemplateBox[{"0"},
     "Ket"]}], "+", 
   RowBox[{
    StyleBox["sin",
     FontSlant->"Plain"], 
    StyleBox["\[Theta]", "TI"], 
    TemplateBox[{"1"},
     "Ket"]}]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "d573a17e-8c08-4c05-bc7e-866fcec7f551"],
 " is fixed by no Pauli and falls outside it. What makes the restriction \
worth a whole subject is that the states it does cover are exactly the ones \
error correction and large parts of quantum algorithms are built from."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"c0e6c9f4-4667-4c31-accb-2eafb39c7e41"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "This deserves a closer look, because \"fixed by no Pauli\" is not the same \
as \"fixed by nothing.\" ",
 StyleBox["Every", "TI"],
 " pure state is the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"+", "1"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "6454f906-2b27-412e-aed7-e9c706e026f7"],
 " eigenstate of some operator. The reflection ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"2", 
    TemplateBox[{
      StyleBox["\[Psi]", "TI"]},
     "Ket"], 
    TemplateBox[{
      StyleBox["\[Psi]", "TI"]},
     "Bra"]}], "-", 
   StyleBox["I", "TI"]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "bd887c37-c1f4-41e3-9245-042fd6e6b500"],
 " does the job for any ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{
    StyleBox["\[Psi]", "TI"]},
   "Ket"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "f94d77dd-5080-4e2c-83f2-3c1cb27ba219"],
 " at all, leaving ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{
    StyleBox["\[Psi]", "TI"]},
   "Ket"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "6b13533b-efbc-4c3a-b2be-be5140035341"],
 " alone and flipping the sign of everything orthogonal to it:"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"7b77c5a3-7b61-4df2-945a-dc07387d6d97"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"psi", " ", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"Cos", "[", 
      RowBox[{"1", "/", "3"}], "]"}], ",", " ", 
     RowBox[{"Sin", "[", 
      RowBox[{"1", "/", "3"}], "]"}]}], "}"}]}], ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"reflection", " ", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"2", " ", 
     RowBox[{"Outer", "[", 
      RowBox[{"Times", ",", " ", "psi", ",", " ", "psi"}], "]"}]}], " ", "-", 
    " ", 
    RowBox[{"IdentityMatrix", "[", "2", "]"}]}]}], ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"Simplify", "[", 
   RowBox[{"reflection", " ", ".", " ", "psi"}], "]"}], " ", "==", " ", 
  "psi"}]}], "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[3]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"66894a02-2de8-4774-a1d9-f9bca7a18e4f"],

Cell[BoxData["True"], "Output",
 CellLabel->"Out[3]= ",ExpressionUUID->"f0dd7b51-01be-44af-a005-ca0d5d64ee23"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell["\<\
That stabilizing operator is a dense, structureless thing that turns \
continuously as the state turns:\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"a4bdb108-87c5-491f-b07d-d944587707cf"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"Simplify", "[", "reflection", "]"}], " ", "//", " ", 
  "MatrixForm"}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[4]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"da9953f2-8bf9-4bb8-80d4-2424aeffc9ee"],

Cell[BoxData[
 TagBox[
  RowBox[{"(", "\[NoBreak]", GridBox[{
     {
      RowBox[{"Cos", "[", 
       FractionBox["2", "3"], "]"}], 
      RowBox[{"Sin", "[", 
       FractionBox["2", "3"], "]"}]},
     {
      RowBox[{"Sin", "[", 
       FractionBox["2", "3"], "]"}], 
      RowBox[{"-", 
       RowBox[{"Cos", "[", 
        FractionBox["2", "3"], "]"}]}]}
    },
    GridBoxAlignment->{"Columns" -> {{Center}}, "Rows" -> {{Baseline}}},
    GridBoxSpacings->{"Columns" -> {
        Offset[0.27999999999999997`], {
         Offset[0.7]}, 
        Offset[0.27999999999999997`]}, "Rows" -> {
        Offset[0.2], {
         Offset[0.4]}, 
        Offset[0.2]}}], "\[NoBreak]", ")"}],
  Function[BoxForm`e$, 
   MatrixForm[BoxForm`e$]]]], "Output",
 CellLabel->"Out[4]= ",ExpressionUUID->"1d0754af-d435-4dd7-ae3c-6b938d69eddd"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
 "So \"a state is what fixes it\" is, on its own, vacuous: this reflection \
takes the full ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SuperscriptBox["2", 
   StyleBox["n", "TI"]]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "8e112a1c-3a4c-4dc0-9157-de43f2f80c70"],
 " amplitudes to write down, exactly the cost we are fleeing, and a gate \
turns it into some other arbitrary operator. The power comes entirely from \
restricting the fixing operators to the ",
 StyleBox["Pauli group", "TI"],
 ", which is special on four counts that only pay off together:"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"1dac2130-328d-4097-8235-64b86f373e5e"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Cheap to name", "TI"],
 ": a Pauli string is ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["O", "TI"], 
   StyleBox["(",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   StyleBox["n", "TI"], 
   StyleBox[")",
    SpanMaxSize->1]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "617863d2-032b-4011-ad00-3f910c7db558"],
 " bits, two per qubit and a sign, not ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SuperscriptBox["2", 
   StyleBox["n", "TI"]]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "9a9c8cb8-33e2-4fec-ab86-6a32a8c0b3dc"],
 " amplitudes."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"00e0de80-f444-4c83-91a5-ba8a7d6e04d1"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Clean spectrum", "TI"],
 ": it squares to the identity, so its eigenvalues are ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"\[PlusMinus]", "1"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "e2ee9abc-1724-4173-97cb-6a86653a66ca"],
 ", and \"fixed by ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["P", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "adda7db8-1144-4781-8a22-18e52176ec10"],
 "\" sharpens to the binary fact \"",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"+", "1"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "1a2158fd-eaf0-44be-8178-e224e628a123"],
 " eigenstate.\""
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"62331143-acb2-4d67-bb22-e3bc362d3262"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Commute or anticommute", "TI"],
 ": any two Paulis do one or the other, with nothing in between, so ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["n", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "571d2e59-697a-4558-834b-46794d31a995"],
 " independent commuting Paulis halve the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SuperscriptBox["2", 
   StyleBox["n", "TI"]]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "109e40cb-5edb-415a-9062-e0ec32504d2a"],
 "-dimensional space ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["n", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "82fc0b07-5779-4990-bc9d-cac0f867a44a"],
 " times and leave a unique joint ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"+", "1"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "d9d47bd1-a6e9-4cc4-80a7-c1a72e19b062"],
 " eigenstate, which is why a list of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["n", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "befe1ac5-63a7-41a8-bfcb-b8002642e71f"],
 " generators pins down one state exactly."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"1e7bb02b-6d67-4fcd-b49e-0a98fb8c23d5"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Closed under Clifford gates", "TI"],
 ": conjugation by ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["H", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "4447f96c-af3a-44af-bffc-f86c5850c7e1"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["S", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "48c97ef5-c9f2-4591-b668-804789e0bd66"],
 ", and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["CNOT",
   FontSlant->"Plain"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "3ac22ff8-970d-4cbf-93b0-5041e9496e5c"],
 " sends Paulis to Paulis, so the description never leaves the Pauli language \
as the state evolves."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"5efab51c-f07e-411b-8975-31aa70b7dd89"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The reflection ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"2", 
    TemplateBox[{
      StyleBox["\[Psi]", "TI"]},
     "Ket"], 
    TemplateBox[{
      StyleBox["\[Psi]", "TI"]},
     "Bra"]}], "-", 
   StyleBox["I", "TI"]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "9b223b5b-a013-4223-b8b0-208e28272d9e"],
 " has none of these properties. Drop any one of them and naming a state by \
what fixes it stops paying its way; keep all four and it becomes the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["O", "TI"], 
   StyleBox["(",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   SuperscriptBox[
    StyleBox["n", "TI"], "2"], 
   StyleBox[")",
    SpanMaxSize->1]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "22cef87b-89e3-4e8f-9072-2a3cc2fe83a0"],
 " tableau the rest of this document runs on."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"0def9ee2-1402-4a91-ac83-82fe384c5dbb"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Verify that ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["Z", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "cb154c7d-62d1-4707-868a-033152c545a8"],
 " fixes ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{"0"},
   "Ket"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "9c61fd39-8c86-4a9c-b62e-2ba41a4d8c48"],
 ", recalling that the built-in ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"PauliMatrix", "[", "1", "]"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "d13a6b2a-24ad-44f9-9cd2-58a1f5ef8a22"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"PauliMatrix", "[", "2", "]"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "7fc8401b-dbe0-474a-9856-8742a511fdfd"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"PauliMatrix", "[", "3", "]"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "0f3812a2-e0a4-42b7-8e51-8243f215439d"],
 " are ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["X", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "ad6c8a46-8e0b-4541-b47a-141c51d1c3b3"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["Y", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "c065c0c4-f26a-462d-b801-8975ca2c67cf"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["Z", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "acd44472-ce86-45f5-94ab-89b51ae763e8"],
 ":"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"9da867a5-deef-4004-9ffe-505d47a6df74"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"PauliMatrix", "[", "3", "]"}], " ", ".", " ", 
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{"1", ",", " ", "0"}], "}"}]}], " ", "==", " ", 
  RowBox[{"{", 
   RowBox[{"1", ",", " ", "0"}], "}"}]}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[5]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"cc07d082-c717-4776-a6ba-3c20bb32130c"],

Cell[BoxData["True"], "Output",
 CellLabel->"Out[5]= ",ExpressionUUID->"d7cce932-d128-44ec-a82e-5494bee0c2fc"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
 "In the framework, the one-qubit register ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{"0"},
   "Ket"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "a1579370-6686-47b6-866e-3042a95bf43d"],
 " is ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"PauliStabilizer", "[", "1", "]"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "fa2d1516-01b8-46d8-835d-f139f22c9486"],
 ". The object prints as a summary box that shows its generators and, for \
small systems, its tableau, so the cheap representation is the thing you \
see:"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"91b59a34-84d1-459d-b0bf-1490b0d84746"],

