  RowBox[{"psiStabilizer", "[", "\"\<StateVector\>\"", "]"}], " ", "//", " ", 
  "Normal"}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->
  "In[37]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"4cde9ef7-ec4d-41f7-b8ce-71f7a0254f09"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"-", 
    FractionBox["\[ImaginaryI]", 
     SqrtBox["2"]]}], ",", "0", ",", "0", ",", "0", ",", "0", ",", "0", ",", 
   "0", ",", 
   FractionBox["1", 
    SqrtBox["2"]]}], "}"}]], "Output",
 CellLabel->
  "Out[37]= ",ExpressionUUID->"61477030-295a-4948-9667-329cd091f1eb"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Rather than chase that phase by hand, compare the two states with the \
framework's ",
 Cell[BoxData["QuantumSimilarity"], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "0c2be58f-5b63-4086-bd33-66a42a4bb96f"],
 ", which is one exactly when they agree up to a global phase:"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"293b2cbc-5569-4419-b8a1-05b4cbe5cdb6"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"QuantumSimilarity", "[", 
  RowBox[{"psiSchrodinger", ",", " ", "psiStabilizer"}], "]"}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->
  "In[38]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"3ce4f63b-36d5-46f8-8749-0192ddd47f25"],

Cell[BoxData["1"], "Output",
 CellLabel->
  "Out[38]= ",ExpressionUUID->"4a580dcf-d4a2-4867-b126-52951724945c"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
 "This is the Gottesman-Knill theorem made concrete: a Clifford circuit on a \
stabilizer input is simulated by propagating ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["n", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "999504e1-a63d-44bd-9911-880bf9aa6f1c"],
 " generators at ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["O", "TI"], 
   StyleBox["(",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   StyleBox["n", "TI"], 
   StyleBox[")",
    SpanMaxSize->1]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "a8f9b9d3-6a6c-40e4-9c45-1475f1c6584b"],
 " work per gate, and the state it computes is exactly the one Schr\
\[ODoubleDot]dinger evolution would, with the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SuperscriptBox["2", 
   StyleBox["n", "TI"]]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "85670d72-32be-4bd5-820e-cc21772cbd68"],
 " vector never formed except, here, to check."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"3a86cf39-b293-4ec9-bdba-c24cac167c13"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The construction rests entirely on Clifford conjugation keeping a Pauli a \
Pauli, so it is also clear where it must break. A non-Clifford gate does not \
respect the Pauli group. The ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["T", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "bfa08dde-e62e-47e7-b207-a192034455a0"],
 " gate commutes with ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["Z", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "7ffa6735-6db5-4137-b341-213f6dfa20a7"],
 ", but conjugating ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["X", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "c88a889f-61b3-4bee-bbd5-59e43952694c"],
 " by it gives a sum. The conjugation ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["T", "TI"], 
   StyleBox["X", "TI"], 
   SuperscriptBox[
    StyleBox["T", "TI"], "\[Dagger]"]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "324be659-e891-4798-8ad2-7a78096123bc"],
 " is cleanest as the circuit ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"{", 
    SuperscriptBox[
     StyleBox["T", "TI"], "\[Dagger]"]}], ",", 
   StyleBox["X", "TI"], ",", 
   RowBox[{
    StyleBox["T", "TI"], "}"}]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "49d7cff4-e99a-4539-b0d9-55807cee77d3"],
 " decomposed into Paulis:"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"95c370d1-cd23-44bf-96fe-93fed42b4974"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"ExpToTrig", " ", "@", " ", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"QuantumCircuitOperator", "[", 
    RowBox[{"{", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"SuperDagger", "[", "\"\<T\>\"", "]"}], ",", " ", "\"\<X\>\"", ",",
       " ", "\"\<T\>\""}], "}"}], "]"}], "[", "\"\<PauliDecompose\>\"", 
   "]"}]}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->
  "In[39]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"f34932d4-4517-42c9-ab68-ecc3e6e034dd"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"\[LeftAssociation]", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"\<\"X\"\>", "\[Rule]", 
    FractionBox["1", 
     SqrtBox["2"]]}], ",", 
   RowBox[{"\<\"Y\"\>", "\[Rule]", 
    FractionBox["1", 
     SqrtBox["2"]]}]}], "\[RightAssociation]"}]], "Output",
 CellLabel->
  "Out[39]= ",ExpressionUUID->"d59d7a42-2131-4c99-9cd4-07e41190421b"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Here ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["T", "TI"], 
   StyleBox["X", "TI"], 
   SuperscriptBox[
    StyleBox["T", "TI"], "\[Dagger]"], "=", 
   StyleBox["(",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   RowBox[{
    StyleBox["X", "TI"], "+", 
    StyleBox["Y", "TI"]}], 
   StyleBox[")",
    SpanMaxSize->1], "/", 
   SqrtBox["2"]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "5838eb8e-028f-413d-8664-8d1db9053fab"],
 " has two terms, not one. A single generator no longer maps to a single \
generator, the group stops being generated by ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["n", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "b135abe9-0388-4b93-8677-f9b742f7904f"],
 " Pauli strings, and the cheap representation fails. That failure is not an \
accident of implementation but the edge of the classically tractable world; \
stabilizer frames push a bounded distance past that edge, at a cost that \
grows with the number of non-Clifford gates."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"a3f3b687-bc53-4799-9acc-782c50625e4e"],

Cell["Entanglement for free: Bell and GHZ", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"d946d3b5-118a-44fa-83b6-2cb7d9bc2948"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Entangled states are not special in this language; they are simply \
stabilizer groups whose generators are not single-qubit operators. The Bell \
state ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{
    SuperscriptBox["\[CapitalPhi]", "+"]},
   "Ket"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "b1311ed8-c30d-45e1-9f35-796a73f5362c"],
 " is prepared from ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{"00"},
   "Ket"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "f9682c3b-9a17-492c-8bbc-1a64479ea9ed"],
 " by a Hadamard and a CNOT, and its stabilizer group is generated by ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox[
   RowBox[{"X", "X"}], "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "0cda9aa8-497c-407c-b733-6fb3816fcdf5"],
 " and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox[
   RowBox[{"Z", "Z"}], "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "377738ed-22e9-4bdf-abf1-7a739f8f8dda"],
 "."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"8e54013a-d571-4a78-abf0-001f2767cbf3"],

Cell["Build the Bell state:", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"aa060311-4e2f-4816-9b0d-a0e196738c65"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"bell", " ", "=", " ", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"PauliStabilizer", "[", "2", "]"}], "[", 
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{"\"\<H\>\"", ",", " ", "\"\<CNOT\>\""}], "}"}], "]"}]}]], "Input",\

 CellLabel->
  "In[40]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"6554dced-b274-4122-aa9c-ac759251cec7"],

