Cell["and read its generators:", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"a7132bd3-cceb-4064-9293-3c5d9441130e"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"bell", "[", "\"\<Stabilizers\>\"", "]"}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->
  "In[41]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"bbfef31b-7885-48b7-887f-6416aceb9c79"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{"\<\"XX\"\>", ",", "\<\"ZZ\"\>"}], "}"}]], "Output",
 CellLabel->
  "Out[41]= ",ExpressionUUID->"c0913e89-1cfe-4452-88c6-97b713a0f06b"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The generators ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox[
   RowBox[{"X", "X"}], "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "950a8644-a2aa-4e92-a382-43074d757607"],
 " and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox[
   RowBox[{"Z", "Z"}], "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "14adc3ff-f0ce-4469-ab4b-a1125a691c0b"],
 " are the familiar parity checks: the two qubits share an ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["X", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "3d1ce35c-2ee1-485a-9680-65cccf5a96e5"],
 "-parity and a ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["Z", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "1771a120-bd7b-4daf-8a49-aee1632b9e77"],
 "-parity, which is precisely what maximal entanglement looks like here. The \
state vector is the textbook one:"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"0001763f-4308-4e31-9b97-6304e569aac1"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"bell", "[", "\"\<State\>\"", "]"}], "[", "\"\<StateVector\>\"", 
   "]"}], " ", "//", " ", "Normal"}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->
  "In[42]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"9bb6d7ca-132f-4909-9acb-bc1519391ab2"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{
   FractionBox["1", 
    SqrtBox["2"]], ",", "0", ",", "0", ",", 
   FractionBox["1", 
    SqrtBox["2"]]}], "}"}]], "Output",
 CellLabel->
  "Out[42]= ",ExpressionUUID->"6af37c54-01e4-4261-a279-4bb48e7ea331"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Entanglement entropy, normally a Schmidt-decomposition computation that \
blows up with system size, has a closed form for stabilizer states. Fattal \
and collaborators showed that the entanglement entropy across a cut ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["A", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "0ed034c6-ee19-43bc-b0a7-5d21b987ee31"],
 " equals the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SubscriptBox["\|01d53d", "2"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "e4fd5445-5d0c-443e-aaf1-b4be6fc95ef8"],
 "-rank of the generators restricted to ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["A", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "2ef39ff9-f833-4e19-bc61-94f53b7533a3"],
 " (for each generator keep only the symplectic columns of the qubits in ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["A", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "999309d6-fa3e-4308-8dcf-4aa6c22d5f78"],
 "), minus ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{
    StyleBox["A", "TI"]},
   "Abs"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "501b96dc-c0fe-4bef-963f-e36b7832169a"],
 ". The framework computes this with ",
 Cell[BoxData["\"\<Entropy\>\""], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "2e93b3e9-c72e-4c9c-a9aa-e93f39c6bb81"],
 ", in ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["O", "TI"], 
   StyleBox["(",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   SuperscriptBox[
    StyleBox["n", "TI"], "3"], 
   StyleBox[")",
    SpanMaxSize->1]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "d737936f-8515-4cbf-b275-9ec850b4bbe8"],
 " and with no dependence on ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{
    StyleBox["A", "TI"]},
   "Abs"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "9af8293f-0b79-484f-975b-383d11c40c38"],
 ". For the Bell state, tracing out one qubit gives one bit of entropy:"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"58282dfa-df0c-4d6d-a2a2-efb7b2aad214"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"bell", "[", 
  RowBox[{"\"\<Entropy\>\"", ",", " ", 
   RowBox[{"{", "1", "}"}]}], "]"}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->
  "In[43]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"00fd5a56-3f81-4c29-899b-ffbbba1e0426"],

Cell[BoxData["1"], "Output",
 CellLabel->
  "Out[43]= ",ExpressionUUID->"f1451c23-ccad-43f8-9f62-b9cbcd8fd0fc"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The payoff is scale. A GHZ state on a thousand qubits is built by one \
Hadamard and a ladder of CNOTs. Build it (the object prints as a compact \
summary, never forming a ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SuperscriptBox["2", "1000"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "ce3498cb-eca6-4848-b5f4-6bf2e16dcc60"],
 " vector):"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"e24a837e-2547-4f41-8df7-99349628ba20"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"ghz", " ", "=", " ", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"PauliStabilizer", "[", "1000", "]"}], "[", 
   RowBox[{"Prepend", "[", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"Table", "[", 
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"\"\<CNOT\>\"", " ", "->", " ", 
        RowBox[{"{", 
         RowBox[{
          RowBox[{"q", " ", "-", " ", "1"}], ",", " ", "q"}], "}"}]}], ",", 
       " ", 
       RowBox[{"{", 
        RowBox[{"q", ",", " ", "2", ",", " ", "1000"}], "}"}]}], "]"}], ",", 
     " ", "\"\<H\>\""}], "]"}], "]"}]}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->
  "In[44]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"2548bcc0-3273-4e0b-b434-7339de4da00f"],

Cell[BoxData[
 TagBox[
  TemplateBox[{
    RowBox[{
      StyleBox[
       TagBox["PauliStabilizer", "SummaryHead"], "NonInterpretableSummary"], 
      StyleBox["[", "NonInterpretableSummary"], 
