}, Open  ]],

Cell["What we have established:", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"fb36964e-ea78-4832-b5d7-8d094c24a1f5"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "An entangled stabilizer state is one whose generators are multi-qubit Pauli \
strings; Bell is ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["\[LeftAngleBracket]",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   RowBox[{
    StyleBox[
     RowBox[{"X", "X"}], "TI"], ",", 
    StyleBox[
     RowBox[{"Z", "Z"}], "TI"]}], "\[VeryThinSpace]", 
   StyleBox["\[RightAngleBracket]",
    SpanMaxSize->1]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "dbc03fa9-0aa9-455a-9bf7-27eb142aeafe"],
 "."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"fa3997eb-44da-4e8b-b454-72b4153182a8"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Entanglement entropy is an ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SubscriptBox["\|01d53d", "2"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "22733a03-b88d-4133-bd1b-5bd5bd950c87"],
 " rank, computable at ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["n", "TI"], "=", "1000"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "840754d7-4053-4a15-bc51-8dba650acd3f"],
 " in milliseconds."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"94183504-4cf2-44b0-9fa2-5b95c7d36f5a"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The cost of all this is ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["O", "TI"], 
   StyleBox["(",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   SuperscriptBox[
    StyleBox["n", "TI"], "2"], 
   StyleBox[")",
    SpanMaxSize->1]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "19da1945-bc94-4d2f-8f2c-179ca0a89f5d"],
 " storage and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["O", "TI"], 
   StyleBox["(",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   SuperscriptBox[
    StyleBox["n", "TI"], "3"], 
   StyleBox[")",
    SpanMaxSize->1]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "57e587d5-46c0-4fd2-adb3-501805f00aa0"],
 " for the rank, never ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["O", "TI"], 
   StyleBox["(",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   SuperscriptBox["2", 
    StyleBox["n", "TI"]], 
   StyleBox[")",
    SpanMaxSize->1]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "61377281-f107-421a-8dfa-60462cd11109"],
 "."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"8cb18f1e-8575-4cd1-a9e8-4388579d20a5"],

Cell["Measurement: randomness, back-action, and correlation", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"3031b363-5974-46d4-b719-6f845af2ca7c"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Measurement is where the destabilizers earn their keep. Measuring ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["Z", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "3880cdf2-fe59-4547-9abf-c842a497e036"],
 " on qubit ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["a", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "03efcbe5-adcb-4496-83a0-2e80bce3a709"],
 " splits into two cases. If ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SubscriptBox[
   StyleBox["Z", "TI"], 
   StyleBox["a", "TI"]]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "21a6aca6-1f5c-4c89-9fcd-98ad83f02be5"],
 " commutes with every stabilizer, then ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"\[PlusMinus]", 
   SubscriptBox[
    StyleBox["Z", "TI"], 
    StyleBox["a", "TI"]]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "af11e69b-fbd4-4a18-8730-e4224298679a"],
 " already lies in the stabilizer group: the outcome is ",
 StyleBox["deterministic", "TI"],
 ", the state is unchanged, and the bit is the sign of the generator product \
that equals ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SubscriptBox[
   StyleBox["Z", "TI"], 
   StyleBox["a", "TI"]]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "9a7fe7e9-b96d-42da-a0fe-d1026fac0826"],
 ", which the destabilizers locate in ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["O", "TI"], 
   StyleBox["(",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   SuperscriptBox[
    StyleBox["n", "TI"], "2"], 
   StyleBox[")",
    SpanMaxSize->1]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "6a398cdc-e2c2-4348-993c-d0117bc32351"],
 ". If instead some stabilizer anticommutes with ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SubscriptBox[
   StyleBox["Z", "TI"], 
   StyleBox["a", "TI"]]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "4df02249-3cc6-4b54-a515-8417f478e261"],
 ", the outcome is a fair coin, and the post-measurement state follows from a \
sequence of Aaronson-Gottesman row sums into one anticommuting generator, \
with a destabilizer as scratch. Either way the work is ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["O", "TI"], 
   StyleBox["(",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   SuperscriptBox[
    StyleBox["n", "TI"], "2"], 
   StyleBox[")",
    SpanMaxSize->1]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "c927bdf1-7a96-488e-ac4b-88ddfc264a38"],
 ", never ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["O", "TI"], 
   StyleBox["(",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   SuperscriptBox["2", 
    StyleBox["n", "TI"]], 
   StyleBox[")",
    SpanMaxSize->1]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "e87148ee-a49d-4491-8673-23b2a2f171ee"],
 "."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"b55af36d-d0dd-4835-82ab-3958b3515928"],

Cell["\<\
A measurement on a stabilizer state returns an association from outcome to \
post-state. For the Bell state, measuring qubit 1 is random, so both branches \
appear:\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"d762d5c4-30b5-4ecd-af7a-823e8e8dc45e"],

